Description:
Ballistics of the 125mm Type-2 Tungsten APFSDS round for use on weapons of the D-81 family, including the ZPT-98-125. This charge design utilized high-nitration nitrocellulose in parallel, and as a backup to the TEGDN based solutions. This was not adopted by the PLA.

Projectile: 125-2 7.44 kg
Charge: 9.24 kg Nitrocellulose (High Nitration, 1046.4 kJ/kg)
The following break down is presumed and based on 125-1 design
 - Main:        6.00 kg 16/19 Rosette
 - Incremental: 3.24 kg
  - 2.54 kg 16/19 Rosette
  - 0.7  kg 19/1-30
Combustible Cartridge: ~1.12 kg + ~0.4 kg ~= 1.6 kg (686.5 kJ/kg)
As tested:  
Velocity        Temp. Pmcp       Corrected
 - 1678.1 m/s  -40°C  439.1 MPa  492 MPa
 - 1727.9 m/s   15°C  485.2 MPa  543 Mpa
 - 1770.3 m/s   50°C  519.3 MPa  582 MPa
